Here is the shape I recommend for each leaf node:
{
  "tag": "1.2 Go-live dates",
  "musthave": true,
  "goodToHave": false,
  "notes": "Tech Go-Live and Business Go-Live with dates and implementation phase.",
  "keywords": ["Go-live dates", "Incremental Reviews"],

  "field_paths": [
    "release.tech_go_live_date",
    "release.business_go_live_date",
    "release.implementation_phase"
  ],
  "check_type": "all_required",
  "expected_type": "date_block",
  "empty_values": ["", null, "N/A", "TBD", "UNKNOWN"],
  "report_as": "Go-live dates",
  "validation_notes": "All three values must be available to mark PRESENT."
}

For nested object sections
Use this when one section is an object and you want to validate internal fields:
{
  "tag": "2.2 Application Stakeholders",
  "musthave": true,
  "goodToHave": false,
  "notes": "List ITAO, Delegate, Lead SA, Cloud Architect, Technical Lead, PMO.",
  "keywords": ["Application Stakeholders"],

  "field_paths": ["stakeholders"],
  "check_type": "object_complete",
  "required_fields": [
    "itao",
    "lead_sa",
    "cloud_architect",
    "technical_lead"
  ],
  "expected_type": "object",
  "empty_values": ["", null, "N/A", "TBD"],
  "report_as": "Application Stakeholders"
}

For list or table sections
Use this for phase tables, ADR tables, approval history, change history:
{
  "tag": "1.1.a Phase Table",
  "musthave": true,
  "goodToHave": false,
  "notes": "Include Phase Number, Approximate Implementation Date, Overview.",
  "keywords": [],

  "field_paths": ["migration.phase_table"],
  "check_type": "min_items",
  "expected_type": "list",
  "min_items": 1,
  "required_fields": [
    "phase_number",
    "implementation_date",
    "overview"
  ],
  "empty_values": ["", null, "N/A", "TBD"],
  "report_as": "Phase Table"
}




